<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1324,951,1497]" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">
This taxon was originally described at the species rank as 
<taxonomicName box="[961,1060,951,976]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="urens">
<emphasis box="[961,1060,951,976]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">A. urens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from a single female specimen (
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" box="[398,492,991,1017]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">MNHN</collectionCode>
) labelled “Ouedi Harrir [
<collectingCountry box="[818,887,991,1017]" name="Syria" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">Syria</collectingCountry>
]” and synonymised by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kerremans" pageId="9" pageNumber="35" refString="Kerremans, C. (1892) Catalogue synonymique des Buprestides decrits de 1758 a 1890. Memoires de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique, 1, 1 - 304." type="journal article" year="1892">
Kerremans (
<number box="[272,333,1031,1057]" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" value="1892.0">1892</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
with 
<taxonomicName box="[423,537,1031,1056]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucens">
<emphasis box="[423,537,1031,1056]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">A. lucens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Since that time, this taxon has remained in synonymy (e. g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Obenberger" box="[264,480,1071,1097]" pageId="9" pageNumber="35" refString="Obenberger, J. (1917) Holarktische Anthaxien. Beitrag zu einer Monographie der Gattung. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, (1916) 82 (A), Heft 8, 1 - 187." type="journal article" year="1917">
Obenberger, 
<number box="[418,480,1071,1097]" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" value="1917.0">1917</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Rikhter" box="[495,661,1071,1097]" pageId="9" pageNumber="35" refString="Rikhter, A. A. (1949) Fauna SSSR. Nasekomye zhestkokrylye. Zlatki (Buprestidae). Tom XIII, vypusk 2, Chast 2, Moskva, Leningrad, Izdatel'stvo Akademii nauk SSSR, 255 pp (in Russian)." type="book" year="1949">
Rikhter, 
<number box="[599,661,1071,1097]" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" value="1949.0">1949</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Curletti" box="[676,845,1071,1097]" pageId="9" pageNumber="35" refString="Curletti, G. (1994) I Buprestidi d'Italia. Catalogo tassonomico, sinonimico, biologico, geonemico. Natura Bresciana, Brescia, Monografie, No. 19, 1 - 318." type="book chapter" year="1994">
Curletti, 
<number box="[783,845,1071,1097]" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bily" box="[860,991,1071,1097]" pageId="9" pageNumber="35" refString="Bily, S. (1997) World catalogue of the genus Anthaxia Eschscholtz, 1829 (Coleopreta, Buprestidae). Folia Heyrovskyana, Supplementum, 2, 3 - 190." type="journal article" year="1997">
Bílý, 
<number box="[928,991,1071,1097]" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, 
<taxonomicName box="[1159,1270,1071,1096]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucens">
<emphasis box="[1159,1270,1071,1096]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">A. lucens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authority="Ganglbauer, 1882" authorityName="Ganglbauer" authorityYear="1882" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" rank="variety" variety="phoenicea">
var. 
<emphasis box="[264,384,1111,1136]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">phoenicea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ganglbauer" box="[395,608,1111,1137]" pageId="9" pageNumber="35" refString="Ganglbauer, L. (1882) Kleinere Mittheilungen. Wiener Entomologische Zeitung 1, 68 - 69." type="journal article" year="1882">
Ganglbauer, 
<number box="[549,608,1111,1137]" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" value="1882.0">1882</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was described from Beyrut (
<collectingCountry box="[964,1032,1111,1137]" name="Syria" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">Syria</collectingCountry>
); according to the Code (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" box="[272,418,1151,1177]" pageId="9" pageNumber="35" refString="ICZN (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature (4 th edidion). International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 273 pp." type="book" year="1999">
<collectionCode box="[272,345,1151,1177]" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">ICZN</collectionCode>
, 
<number box="[358,418,1151,1177]" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) this name is unavailable since the author described this “variety” evidently as an infrasubspecific taxon. According to Ganglbauer´s description (he did not designate 
<typeStatus box="[264,314,1231,1257]" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">type</typeStatus>
specimens), this “variety” is identical with 
<taxonomicName box="[827,1006,1231,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="lucens" subSpecies="urens">
<emphasis box="[827,1006,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">A. lucens urens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1324,951,1497]" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">
After having studied the 
<typeStatus box="[607,709,1271,1297]" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[750,848,1271,1296]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="urens">
<emphasis box="[750,848,1271,1296]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">A. urens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, I found characters (see key above) that enable the resurrection of this taxon as a distinct, well­characterized, eastern subspecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[264,371,1351,1376]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucens">
<emphasis box="[264,371,1351,1376]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">A. lucens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
